Session state remembers data between that session only Streamlit app reruns.
1-Saves data when app refreshes in same browser tab.
2-Like a dict: st.session_state['name'] = 'value'.
3-Check first: if 'count' not in st.session_state: count = 0.

import streamlit as st

st.session_state.name= "dhairyA"
st.session_state["SURNAME"]="DESAI"
st.session_state.get("age","25")

st.write(
st.session_state.name,
st.session_state["SURNAME"],
st.session_state.get("age","25")
)

--------------  O/P  --------->
dhairyA DESAI 25
